+## 2026-07-16 Australia/Sydney - ADP V0.1 task ADP-S1-P02-T015 (Source Drift CI; S1-P02 complete)
+
+- Fifteenth task of the ADP V0.1 FINAL EXECUTION program and the last of S1-P02 (Source Registry single source truth), one task per run. Goal: block a new hand-written source array, UI label drift, and D1/runtime sources not registered in the Registry. NOT_DEPLOYED, 0 recurring cloud cost; a read-only repo scan, no worker/D1 change. Deliverables under arxiv-daily-push/docs/pursuing_goal/v0_1/: tools/check_source_drift.py (repo scanner allowing exactly one approved source array; runtime/D1 comparison of the worker source-id set vs compiled/runtime.json; UI label drift via ui_labels.registry_hash == compiled registry_hash) and SOURCE_DRIFT_EXCEPTIONS.yaml (approved: the worker REGISTRY is the single source array; no unregistered ids). Acceptance verified (evidence/ADP-S1-P02-T015/test-results/drift_ci_tests.txt): the real worker PASSES with no false positive (one approved array, worker 33 == runtime 33, ui hash matches); injecting a second source array REGISTRY2 with an unregistered id rogue-src makes CI DRIFT (flags both the unapproved array and the live-not-registered id); mutating ui_labels.registry_hash makes CI DRIFT (labels not regenerated from the current registry); and restoring returns PASS. This completes S1-P02: schema (T012) -> migration (T013) -> deterministic compiler (T014) -> drift CI (T015), so DRIFT-FACT-006-class source drift cannot silently return. Cost (unknown != 0): new_requests 0, D1 0 (repo scan), R2 0, model_calls 0. Ends IMPLEMENTATION_READY_FOR_INDEPENDENT_VERIFICATION.
+
 ## 2026-07-16 Australia/Sydney - ADP V0.1 task ADP-S1-P02-T014 (Registry compiler + deterministic output)
 
 - Fourteenth task of the ADP V0.1 FINAL EXECUTION program (S1-P02), one task per run. Goal: from one source generate the runtime, UI labels, D1 seed, health and backfill plan. NOT_DEPLOYED, 0 recurring cloud cost; the seed is a compiled artifact and is NOT applied to production D1. Deliverables under arxiv-daily-push/docs/pursuing_goal/v0_1/: tools/compile_registry.py (the compiler, which first runs the T012 validator plus hard checks, then emits deterministic outputs) and compiled/{runtime.json, ui_labels.json, seed.sql, registry_hash.txt}. Acceptance verified (evidence/ADP-S1-P02-T014/test-results/compile_tests.txt): two consecutive compiles of source_registry.json are byte-identical (registry_hash sha256:d63cf6bd4d72...e7fb; outputs sorted by source_id with sorted keys and no timestamps); and the compiler FAILS on a duplicate source_id, a non-boolean enabled, and an unknown authority_kind. This puts the mechanism to eliminate multiple source truths in place (T013 recorded the migration; T014 generates runtime/UI/seed from the one Registry), and the registry_hash anchors the T015 source drift CI. Cost (unknown != 0): new_requests 0, D1 rows 0 (seed not applied), R2 0, model_calls 0. Ends IMPLEMENTATION_READY_FOR_INDEPENDENT_VERIFICATION.
